    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Colchicine levels do not return in a timely manner\nNo correlation with severity of illness\n>3.0ng/ml generally associated with toxicity\nBMP\nIncluding calcium, magnesium, and phosphorus\nLFTs\nCBC\nCoagulation factors\nCPK\nUrinalysis\nEKG\nCXR\nDepending on clinical situation\nTroponin\nABG\nLactate\nFibrinogen",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Urinalysis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Urinalysis"
        },
        {
          "text": "Troponin",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Troponin"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Supportive care\nGI Decontamination\nOro\ngastric lavage\nin patients who present within 1-2 hours without vomiting\nActivated charcoal\nand consider\nMultidose activated charcoal\nAntidotal therapy\nColchine-specific Fab fragments\nNot commercially available\nGranulocyte-colony stimulating factor (G-CSF)\nuseful in treating patients who develop leukopenia and thrombocytopenia\nExtracorporeal elimination\nNo benefit",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "gastric lavage",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Gastric_lavage"
        },
        {
          "text": "Activated charcoal",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Activated_charcoal"
        },
        {
          "text": "Multidose activated charcoal",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Multidose_activated_charcoal"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "All symptomatic patients require admission to ICU\nPatients who do not develop GI symptoms within 8-12 hours after ingestion likely have not developed significant poisoning\nConsult Toxicology or\npoison control",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
